Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, marked proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and brown, cloudy urine. These findings suggest impaired renal function, likely chronic kidney disease with possible nephrotic features and tubular dysfunction. No evidence of urinary tract infection is present. Blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, so diabetes is unlikely. Recommend urgent nephrology evaluation and further workup for underlying renal pathology.
